Deutsche Bank AG , Germanyâ€™s largest
bank, said its takeover offer for  Deutsche Postbank AG  starts
today and ends on Nov. 4.  Deutsche Bank plans to consolidate Postbank by the end of
this year, the Frankfurt-based lender said in a  statement  on its
website today.  The German bank, led by Chief Executive Officer  Josef Ackermann , confirmed a plan to offer 25 euros a share in cash to
Postbank investors to increase its 29.95 percent stake in the
Bonn-based lender. Deutsche Bank yesterday completed a record
10.2 billion-euro ($14.2 billion) share sale to fund the
takeover of  Postbank  and increase reserves.  To contact the reporter on this story:
